reports.title: NVD Severity by Year 2018 to 2021
reports.query:
MATCH (n:nvdCve)
WHERE n.cve_year <> 2022
RETURN
n.cve_year as Year,
n.severity as Severity,
count(n) as Vulns
ORDER by n.cve_year

reports.title: Academia

MATCH (n:`academia`) 
WHERE toLower(toString(n.`org_id`)) CONTAINS toLower($input) 
RETURN DISTINCT n.`org_id` as value LIMIT 5

reports.title: Software for Academia
reports.query:
MATCH (n:academia)-[i:INSTALLS]-(s:software) 
where n.org_id=$neodash_academia_org_id
RETURN *

reports.title: Academia:  Vulnerabilities by Year & Product
reports.query:
MATCH (o:academia)-[:INSTALLS]-(ss:software)
WITH ss, collect(distinct ss.product) as orgProducts
// Get the individual products in the collection
UNWIND orgProducts as orgProduct
// Find associated vulnerabilities in a particular year
MATCH (o:academia)-[:INSTALLS]-(ss:software)-[:HAS_VERSION]-(n:cpe {product:orgProduct})-[:AFFECTS]-(b:nvdCve)
where o.org_id=$neodash_academia_org_id
and b.cve_year= $neodash_nvdcve_cve_year 
RETURN b.cve_year as Year, 
b.cve_month as Month,
n.product as Product, 
count(distinct b.cve_id) as Vulns 
ORDER by b.cve_year asc, 
b.cve_month ASC,
Vulns desc

reports.title: Top 10 Vendor Vulnerabilities by Year
reports.query:
match (n:nvdCve)-[]-(p:cpe) 
where n.cve_year= $neodash_nvdcve_cve_year
return distinct p.vendor as Vendor, 
count(distinct p.product) as Products, count(n.cve_id) as Vulns 
order by Vulns DESC
LIMIT 10

reports.title: Countries Targeted by Any Threat Group
reports.query: MATCH p=()-[r:TARGETS]-() RETURN p

reports.title: Top 10 Targeted Countries by Threat Group Origin
reports.query:
MATCH (g:attackGroups),(n:targetCountry), (t:countries)
WHERE g.group_id = n.group_id
and g.group_country=$neodash_countries_country
and n.country = t.country
MERGE (g)-[r:TARGETS]->(t)
RETURN t.country as Country, count(g) as ThreatGroups 
order by ThreatGroups desc
limit 10

reports.title: Linking Threat Groups in Given Country to Specific Vulns
reports.query:
MATCH (n:nvdCve )-[w:WEAKENED_BY]-(c:cwe)-[k:KNOWN_ATTACK]-(ca:capec)-[e:EMPLOYS]-(a:attackEnterpriseTechniques)-[r:ACHIEVES_GOAL]-(ag:attackGroups)-[o:ORIGINATES]-(co:countries {country:$neodash_countries_country} )
WHERE n.cve_year= $neodash_nvdcve_cve_year 
OPTIONAL MATCH (ag:attackGroups)-[:TARGETS]-(co2:countries) 
OPTIONAL MATCH (n:nvdCve)-[re:REFERENCE_EXPLOITS]-(edb:exploitDb)
OPTIONAL MATCH (n:nvdCve)-[ex:EXPLOITS_KNOWN]-(cec:cisaExploitCatalog)
OPTIONAL MATCH (ag:attackGroups)-[fo:FOCUS_ON]-(dhs:dhsSectors)
RETURN * 
LIMIT 10000

reports.title: Vulns per Year Targeted by Threat Group in Given Country
reports.query:
MATCH path=(n:nvdCve )-[w:WEAKENED_BY]-(c:cwe)-[k:KNOWN_ATTACK]-(ca:capec)-[e:EMPLOYS]-(a:attackEnterpriseTechniques)-[r:ACHIEVES_GOAL]-(ag:attackGroups)-[o:ORIGINATES]-(co:countries {country:$neodash_countries_country} )
WHERE n.cve_year= $neodash_nvdcve_cve_year 
OPTIONAL MATCH (ag:attackGroups)-[:TARGETS]-(co2:countries)
RETURN ag.group_name as ThreatGroup, count(DISTINCT n.cve_id) as Vulns
LIMIT 10000

reports.title: Threat Group Country of Origin and Countries Targeted
reports.query:
match (g1:attackGroups)-[o:ORIGINATES]-(c1:countries {country:$neodash_countries_country}),
(g2:attackGroups)-[t:TARGETS]-(c2:countries)
return 
{id: g1.group_name, label:"Origin", point:point({longitude: toFloat(c1.longitude), latitude: toFloat(c1.latitude)})},
{id: g2.group_name, label:"Target", point:point({longitude: toFloat(c2.longitude), latitude: toFloat(c2.latitude)})},
{start: g1.group_name, end: g2.group_name, type: "ORIGINATES", id: 1}
LIMIT 10000

reports.title: Vulns Per Month by Threat Group in Given Country and Year
reports.query:
MATCH path=(n:nvdCve )-[w:WEAKENED_BY]-(c:cwe)-[k:KNOWN_ATTACK]-(ca:capec)-[e:EMPLOYS]-(a:attackEnterpriseTechniques)-[r:ACHIEVES_GOAL]-(ag:attackGroups)-[o:ORIGINATES]-(co:countries {country:$neodash_countries_country} )
WHERE n.cve_year= $neodash_nvdcve_cve_year 
RETURN ag.group_name as ThreatGroup, n.cve_month as Month, count(DISTINCT n.cve_id) as Vulns
order by n.cve_month ASC
LIMIT 10000

Academia: Vulnerable to Threat Groups
reports.query:
// Map Threat Groups to Vulns
// Retrieve the software in use by this organization
MATCH (o:organizations:academia)-[:INSTALLS]-(ss:software)
WHERE o.org_id=$neodash_academia_org_id
WITH  ss, collect(distinct ss.product) as orgProducts
// Get the individual products in the collection
UNWIND orgProducts as orgProduct
// Find associated vulnerabilities in a particular year
MATCH (n:nvdCve)-[w:WEAKENED_BY]-(c:cwe)-[k:KNOWN_ATTACK]-(ca:capec)-[e:EMPLOYS]-(a:attackEnterpriseTechniques)-[r:ACHIEVES_GOAL]-(ag:attackGroups)-[o:ORIGINATES]-(co:countries {country:$neodash_countries_country} )
WHERE n.cve_year= $neodash_nvdcve_cve_year 
MATCH (n:nvdCve)-[af:AFFECTS]-(p:cpe {product:orgProduct})
MATCH (ag:attackGroups)-[t:TARGETS]-(co2:countries {country: $neodash_targetcountry_country }) 
RETURN DISTINCT ag.group_name as ThreatGroup, 
p.vendor as Vendor,
p.product as Product,
n.cve_id as CVE_ID, 
n.cvss_base_score as baseScore
ORDER by baseScore DESC, CVE_ID
LIMIT 1000

reports.title: Academia: CVSS Base Score
reports.query:
MATCH (o:organizations:academia)-[:INSTALLS]-(ss:software)
WHERE o.org_id=$neodash_academia_org_id
WITH ss, collect(distinct ss.product) as orgProducts
// Get the individual products in the collection
UNWIND orgProducts as orgProduct
// Find associated vulnerabilities in a particular year
MATCH (o:organizations:academia)-[:INSTALLS]-(ss:software)-[]-(n:cpe {product:orgProduct})-[]-(b:nvdCve) 
WHERE o.org_id=$neodash_academia_org_id
and b.cve_year= $neodash_nvdcve_cve_year

RETURN o.org_id as Org, b.cve_id as Vuln, n.vendor as Vendor,n.product as Product, MAX(n.version) as Version, b.cvss_base_score as BaseScore ORDER by b.cvss_base_score DESC LIMIT 50
